          <text><![CDATA[<p> <b>Drone Operator Safety Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to make it a crime to operate an unmanned aircraft (i.e., drone) that knowingly or recklessly interferes with or disrupts the operation of an aircraft carrying one or more occupants in U.S. airspace.</p> <p>The prohibition includes the operation of an unmanned aircraft within the runway exclusion zone (i.e., defined area of controlled airspace around an active runway) of an airport without approval.</p> <p>A violator is subject to a fine, a prison term, or both.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-12-15T16:21:41Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDate>2016-04-12</actionDate>
        </item>
